-- BOJ extends additional funds to banks in quake-hit areas
-- 
-- Mon Mar 14, 2011 5:56am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/03/14/us-japan-economy-shirakawa-idUSTRE72D2CJ20110314

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - The Bank of Japan supplied an additional 41 billion yen ($500 million) on Monday to financial institutions operating in areas hit by Friday's massive earthquake. 

 It said the move was at the companies' request. The BOJ also said no glitches were reported in major financial institutions' system connection to the central bank on Monday. ($1 = 81.915 Japanese Yen) (Reporting by Rie Ishiguro)